{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm a cancer doctor, and I walked out of my office"},{"time":3000,"text":"and walked by the pharmacy in the hospital three or four years ago,"},{"time":7000,"text":"and this was the cover of Fortune magazine"},{"time":10000,"text":"sitting in the window of the pharmacy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12000,"text":"And so, as a cancer doctor, you look at this,"},{"time":14000,"text":"and you get a little bit downhearted."},{"time":16000,"text":"But when you start to read the article by Cliff,"},{"time":19000,"text":"who himself is a cancer survivor,"},{"time":21000,"text":"who was saved by a clinical trial"},{"time":23000,"text":"where his parents drove him from New York City to upstate New York"},{"time":27000,"text":"to get an experimental therapy for --"},{"time":29000,"text":"at the time -- Hodgkin's disease, which saved his life,"},{"time":32000,"text":"he makes remarkable points here."},{"time":35000,"text":"And the point of the article was that we have gotten"},{"time":38000,"text":"reductionist in our view of biology,"},{"time":41000,"text":"in our view of cancer."},{"time":43000,"text":"For the last 50 years, we have focused on treating"},{"time":46000,"text":"the individual gene"},{"time":48000,"text":"in understanding cancer, not in controlling cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"So, this is an astounding table."},{"time":54000,"text":"And this is something that sobers us in our field everyday"},{"time":57000,"text":"in that, obviously, we've made remarkable impacts"},{"time":59000,"text":"on cardiovascular disease,"},{"time":61000,"text":"but look at cancer. The death rate in cancer"},{"time":64000,"text":"in over 50 years hasn't changed."},{"time":67000,"text":"We've made small wins in diseases like chronic myelogenous leukemia,"},{"time":71000,"text":"where we have a pill that can put 100 percent of people in remission,"},{"time":74000,"text":"but in general, we haven't made an impact at all in the war on cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80000,"text":"So, what I'm going to tell you today,"},{"time":83000,"text":"is a little bit of why I think that's the case,"},{"time":86000,"text":"and then go out of my comfort zone"},{"time":88000,"text":"and tell you where I think it's going,"},{"time":91000,"text":"where a new approach -- that we hope to push forward"},{"time":94000,"text":"in terms of treating cancer."},{"time":98000,"text":"Because this is wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101000,"text":"So, what is cancer, first of all?"},{"time":103000,"text":"Well, if one has a mass or an abnormal blood value, you go to a doctor,"},{"time":108000,"text":"they stick a needle in."},{"time":110000,"text":"They way we make the diagnosis today is by pattern recognition:"},{"time":114000,"text":"Does it look normal? Does it look abnormal?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"So, that pathologist is just like looking at this plastic bottle."},{"time":121000,"text":"This is a normal cell. This is a cancer cell."},{"time":124000,"text":"That is the state-of-the-art today in diagnosing cancer."},{"time":129000,"text":"There's no molecular test,"},{"time":132000,"text":"there's no sequencing of genes that was referred to yesterday,"},{"time":135000,"text":"there's no fancy looking at the chromosomes."},{"time":138000,"text":"This is the state-of-the-art and how we do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"You know, I know very well, as a cancer doctor, I can't treat advanced cancer."},{"time":147000,"text":"So, as an aside, I firmly believe in the field of trying to identify cancer early."},{"time":154000,"text":"It is the only way you can start to fight cancer, is by catching it early."},{"time":159000,"text":"We can prevent most cancers."},{"time":162000,"text":"You know, the previous talk alluded to preventing heart disease."},{"time":165000,"text":"We could do the same in cancer."},{"time":167000,"text":"I co-founded a company called Navigenics,"},{"time":169000,"text":"where, if you spit into a tube --"},{"time":171000,"text":"and we can look look at 35 or 40 genetic markers for disease,"},{"time":177000,"text":"all of which are delayable in many of the cancers --"},{"time":179000,"text":"you start to identify what you could get,"},{"time":183000,"text":"and then we can start to work to prevent them."},{"time":186000,"text":"Because the problem is, when you have advanced cancer,"},{"time":189000,"text":"we can't do that much today about it, as the statistics allude to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193000,"text":"So, the thing about cancer is that it's a disease of the aged."},{"time":197000,"text":"Why is it a disease of the aged?"},{"time":199000,"text":"Because evolution doesn't care about us after we've had our children."},{"time":204000,"text":"See, evolution protected us during our childbearing years"},{"time":207000,"text":"and then, after age 35 or 40 or 45,"},{"time":211000,"text":"it said \"It doesn't matter anymore, because they've had their progeny.\""},{"time":215000,"text":"So if you look at cancers, it is very rare -- extremely rare --"},{"time":220000,"text":"to have cancer in a child, on the order of thousands of cases a year."},{"time":225000,"text":"As one gets older? Very, very common."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"Why is it hard to treat?"},{"time":231000,"text":"Because it's heterogeneous,"},{"time":233000,"text":"and that's the perfect substrate for evolution within the cancer."},{"time":238000,"text":"It starts to select out for those bad, aggressive cells,"},{"time":242000,"text":"what we call clonal selection."},{"time":246000,"text":"But, if we start to understand"},{"time":249000,"text":"that cancer isn't just a molecular defect, it's something more,"},{"time":254000,"text":"then we'll get to new ways of treating it, as I'll show you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"So, one of the fundamental problems we have in cancer"},{"time":260000,"text":"is that, right now, we describe it by a number of adjectives, symptoms:"},{"time":264000,"text":"\"I'm tired, I'm bloated, I have pain, etc.\""},{"time":267000,"text":"You then have some anatomic descriptions,"},{"time":269000,"text":"you get that CT scan: \"There's a three centimeter mass in the liver.\""},{"time":273000,"text":"You then have some body part descriptions:"},{"time":276000,"text":"\"It's in the liver, in the breast, in the prostate.\""},{"time":278000,"text":"And that's about it."},{"time":281000,"text":"So, our dictionary for describing cancer is very, very poor."},{"time":285000,"text":"It's basically symptoms."},{"time":287000,"text":"It's manifestations of a disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290000,"text":"What's exciting is that over the last two or three years,"},{"time":293000,"text":"the government has spent 400 million dollars,"},{"time":295000,"text":"and they've allocated another billion dollars,"},{"time":298000,"text":"to what we call the Cancer Genome Atlas Project."},{"time":300000,"text":"So, it is the idea of sequencing all of the genes in the cancer,"},{"time":304000,"text":"and giving us a new lexicon, a new dictionary to describe it."},{"time":309000,"text":"You know, in the mid-1850's in France,"},{"time":312000,"text":"they started to describe cancer by body part."},{"time":315000,"text":"That hasn't changed in over 150 years."},{"time":319000,"text":"It is absolutely archaic that we call cancer"},{"time":323000,"text":"by prostate, by breast, by muscle."},{"time":327000,"text":"It makes no sense, if you think about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330000,"text":"So, obviously, the technology is here today,"},{"time":333000,"text":"and, over the next several years, that will change."},{"time":336000,"text":"You will no longer go to a breast cancer clinic."},{"time":338000,"text":"You will go to a HER2 amplified clinic, or an EGFR activated clinic,"},{"time":343000,"text":"and they will go to some of the pathogenic lesions"},{"time":345000,"text":"that were involved in causing this individual cancer."},{"time":349000,"text":"So, hopefully, we will go from being the art of medicine"},{"time":352000,"text":"more to the science of medicine,"},{"time":354000,"text":"and be able to do what they do in infectious disease,"},{"time":357000,"text":"which is look at that organism, that bacteria,"},{"time":360000,"text":"and then say, \"This antibiotic makes sense,"},{"time":363000,"text":"because you have a particular bacteria that will respond to it.\""},{"time":367000,"text":"When one is exposed to H1N1, you take Tamiflu,"},{"time":371000,"text":"and you can remarkably decrease the severity of symptoms"},{"time":374000,"text":"and prevent many of the manifestations of the disease."},{"time":377000,"text":"Why? Because we know what you have, and we know how to treat it --"},{"time":382000,"text":"although we can't make vaccine in this country, but that's a different story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386000,"text":"The Cancer Genome Atlas is coming out now."},{"time":389000,"text":"The first cancer was done, which was brain cancer."},{"time":393000,"text":"In the next month, the end of December, you'll see ovarian cancer,"},{"time":397000,"text":"and then lung cancer will come several months after."},{"time":401000,"text":"There's also a field of proteomics that I'll talk about in a few minutes,"},{"time":404000,"text":"which I think is going to be the next level"},{"time":407000,"text":"in terms of understanding and classifying disease."},{"time":411000,"text":"But remember, I'm not pushing genomics,"},{"time":413000,"text":"proteomics, to be a reductionist."},{"time":416000,"text":"I'm doing it so we can identify what we're up against."},{"time":419000,"text":"And there's a very important distinction there that we'll get to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423000,"text":"In health care today, we spend most of the dollars --"},{"time":426000,"text":"in terms of treating disease --"},{"time":429000,"text":"most of the dollars in the last two years of a person's life."},{"time":433000,"text":"We spend very little, if any, dollars in terms of identifying what we're up against."},{"time":438000,"text":"If you could start to move that, to identify what you're up against,"},{"time":442000,"text":"you're going to do things a hell of a lot better."},{"time":445000,"text":"If we could even take it one step further and prevent disease,"},{"time":449000,"text":"we can take it enormously the other direction,"},{"time":452000,"text":"and obviously, that's where we need to go, going forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456000,"text":"So, this is the website of the National Cancer Institute."},{"time":459000,"text":"And I'm here to tell you, it's wrong."},{"time":462000,"text":"So, the website of the National Cancer Institute"},{"time":464000,"text":"says that cancer is a genetic disease."},{"time":468000,"text":"The website says, \"If you look, there's an individual mutation,"},{"time":472000,"text":"and maybe a second, and maybe a third,"},{"time":474000,"text":"and that is cancer.\""},{"time":476000,"text":"But, as a cancer doc, this is what I see."},{"time":480000,"text":"This isn't a genetic disease."},{"time":482000,"text":"So, there you see, it's a liver with colon cancer in it,"},{"time":485000,"text":"and you see into the microscope a lymph node"},{"time":487000,"text":"where cancer has invaded."},{"time":489000,"text":"You see a CT scan where cancer is in the liver."},{"time":493000,"text":"Cancer is an interaction of a cell"},{"time":496000,"text":"that no longer is under growth control with the environment."},{"time":501000,"text":"It's not in the abstract; it's the interaction with the environment."},{"time":505000,"text":"It's what we call a system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"The goal of me as a cancer doctor is not to understand cancer."},{"time":512000,"text":"And I think that's been the fundamental problem over the last five decades,"},{"time":515000,"text":"is that we have strived to understand cancer."},{"time":518000,"text":"The goal is to control cancer."},{"time":521000,"text":"And that is a very different optimization scheme,"},{"time":523000,"text":"a very different strategy for all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526000,"text":"I got up at the American Association of Cancer Research,"},{"time":528000,"text":"one of the big cancer research meetings, with 20,000 people there,"},{"time":532000,"text":"and I said, \"We've made a mistake."},{"time":535000,"text":"We've all made a mistake, myself included,"},{"time":538000,"text":"by focusing down, by being a reductionist."},{"time":540000,"text":"We need to take a step back.\""},{"time":542000,"text":"And, believe it or not, there were hisses in the audience."},{"time":544000,"text":"People got upset, but this is the only way we're going to go forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548000,"text":"You know, I was very fortunate to meet Danny Hillis a few years ago."},{"time":552000,"text":"We were pushed together, and neither one of us really wanted to meet the other."},{"time":556000,"text":"I said, \"Do I really want to meet a guy from Disney, who designed computers?\""},{"time":560000,"text":"And he was saying: Does he really want to meet another doctor?"},{"time":563000,"text":"But people prevailed on us, and we got together,"},{"time":565000,"text":"and it's been transformative in what I do, absolutely transformative."},{"time":571000,"text":"We have designed, and we have worked on the modeling --"},{"time":574000,"text":"and much of these ideas came from Danny and from his team --"},{"time":578000,"text":"the modeling of cancer in the body as complex system."},{"time":581000,"text":"And I'll show you some data there"},{"time":583000,"text":"where I really think it can make a difference and a new way to approach it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587000,"text":"The key is, when you look at these variables and you look at this data,"},{"time":591000,"text":"you have to understand the data inputs."},{"time":595000,"text":"You know, if I measured your temperature over 30 days,"},{"time":599000,"text":"and I asked, \"What was the average temperature?\""},{"time":601000,"text":"and it came back at 98.7, I would say, \"Great.\""},{"time":605000,"text":"But if during one of those days"},{"time":607000,"text":"your temperature spiked to 102 for six hours,"},{"time":610000,"text":"and you took Tylenol and got better, etc.,"},{"time":612000,"text":"I would totally miss it."},{"time":614000,"text":"So, one of the problems, the fundamental problems in medicine"},{"time":617000,"text":"is that you and I, and all of us,"},{"time":619000,"text":"we go to our doctor once a year."},{"time":621000,"text":"We have discrete data elements; we don't have a time function on them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625000,"text":"Earlier it was referred to this direct life device."},{"time":628000,"text":"You know, I've been using it for two and a half months."},{"time":631000,"text":"It's a staggering device, not because it tells me"},{"time":633000,"text":"how many kilocalories I do every day,"},{"time":636000,"text":"but because it looks, over 24 hours, what I've done in a day."},{"time":640000,"text":"And I didn't realize that for three hours I'm sitting at my desk,"},{"time":643000,"text":"and I'm not moving at all."},{"time":645000,"text":"And a lot of the functions in the data that we have as input systems here"},{"time":650000,"text":"are really different than we understand them,"},{"time":653000,"text":"because we're not measuring them dynamically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655000,"text":"And so, if you think of cancer as a system,"},{"time":660000,"text":"there's an input and an output and a state in the middle."},{"time":664000,"text":"So, the states, are equivalent classes of history,"},{"time":667000,"text":"and the cancer patient, the input, is the environment,"},{"time":670000,"text":"the diet, the treatment, the genetic mutations."},{"time":674000,"text":"The output are our symptoms:"},{"time":677000,"text":"Do we have pain? Is the cancer growing? Do we feel bloated, etc.?"},{"time":681000,"text":"Most of that state is hidden."},{"time":685000,"text":"So what we do in our field is we change and input,"},{"time":688000,"text":"we give aggressive chemotherapy,"},{"time":690000,"text":"and we say, \"Did that output get better? Did that pain improve, etc.?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":695000,"text":"And so, the problem is that it's not just one system,"},{"time":699000,"text":"it's multiple systems on multiple scales."},{"time":702000,"text":"It's a system of systems."},{"time":705000,"text":"And so, when you start to look at emergent systems,"},{"time":707000,"text":"you can look at a neuron under a microscope."},{"time":710000,"text":"A neuron under the microscope is very elegant"},{"time":712000,"text":"with little things sticking out and little things over here,"},{"time":715000,"text":"but when you start to put them together in a complex system,"},{"time":719000,"text":"and you start to see that it becomes a brain,"},{"time":721000,"text":"and that brain can create intelligence,"},{"time":724000,"text":"what we're talking about in the body,"},{"time":726000,"text":"and cancer is starting to model it like a complex system."},{"time":729000,"text":"Well, the bad news is that these robust --"},{"time":732000,"text":"and robust is a key word --"},{"time":734000,"text":"emergent systems are very hard to understand in detail."},{"time":738000,"text":"The good news is you can manipulate them."},{"time":741000,"text":"You can try to control them"},{"time":743000,"text":"without that fundamental understanding of every component."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746000,"text":"One of the most fundamental clinical trials in cancer"},{"time":749000,"text":"came out in February in the New England Journal of Medicine,"},{"time":752000,"text":"where they took women who were pre-menopausal with breast cancer."},{"time":756000,"text":"So, about the worst kind of breast cancer you can get."},{"time":759000,"text":"They had gotten their chemotherapy,"},{"time":761000,"text":"and then they randomized them,"},{"time":763000,"text":"where half got placebo,"},{"time":765000,"text":"and half got a drug called Zoledronic acid that builds bone."},{"time":769000,"text":"It's used to treat osteoporosis,"},{"time":771000,"text":"and they got that twice a year."},{"time":773000,"text":"They looked and, in these 1,800 women,"},{"time":777000,"text":"given twice a year a drug that builds bone,"},{"time":780000,"text":"you reduce the recurrence of cancer by 35 percent."},{"time":786000,"text":"Reduce occurrence of cancer by a drug"},{"time":788000,"text":"that doesn't even touch the cancer."},{"time":790000,"text":"So the notion, you change the soil, the seed doesn't grow as well."},{"time":795000,"text":"You change that system,"},{"time":798000,"text":"and you could have a marked effect on the cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800000,"text":"Nobody has ever shown -- and this will be shocking --"},{"time":803000,"text":"nobody has ever shown that most chemotherapy"},{"time":806000,"text":"actually touches a cancer cell."},{"time":808000,"text":"It's never been shown."},{"time":810000,"text":"There's all these elegant work in the tissue culture dishes,"},{"time":813000,"text":"that if you give this cancer drug, you can do this effect to the cell,"},{"time":816000,"text":"but the doses in those dishes are nowhere near"},{"time":819000,"text":"the doses that happen in the body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823000,"text":"If I give a woman with breast cancer a drug called Taxol"},{"time":826000,"text":"every three weeks, which is the standard,"},{"time":828000,"text":"about 40 percent of women with metastatic cancer"},{"time":830000,"text":"have a great response to that drug."},{"time":833000,"text":"And a response is 50 percent shrinkage."},{"time":835000,"text":"Well, remember that's not even an order of magnitude,"},{"time":837000,"text":"but that's a different story."},{"time":839000,"text":"They then recur, I give them that same drug every week."},{"time":843000,"text":"Another 30 percent will respond."},{"time":846000,"text":"They then recur, I give them that same drug"},{"time":848000,"text":"over 96 hours by continuous infusion,"},{"time":851000,"text":"another 20 or 30 percent will respond."},{"time":854000,"text":"So, you can't tell me it's working by the same mechanism in all three size."},{"time":858000,"text":"It's not. We have no idea the mechanism."},{"time":861000,"text":"So the idea that chemotherapy may just be disrupting"},{"time":864000,"text":"that complex system,"},{"time":867000,"text":"just like building bone disrupted that system and reduced recurrence,"},{"time":872000,"text":"chemotherapy may work by that same exact way."},{"time":875000,"text":"The wild thing about that trial also,"},{"time":878000,"text":"was that it reduced new primaries, so new cancers, by 30 percent also."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887000,"text":"So, the problem is, yours and mine, all of our systems are changing."},{"time":892000,"text":"They're dynamic."},{"time":894000,"text":"I mean, this is a scary slide, not to take an aside,"},{"time":897000,"text":"but it looks at obesity in the world."},{"time":899000,"text":"And I'm sorry if you can't read the numbers, they're kind of small."},{"time":902000,"text":"But, if you start to look at it, that red, that dark color there,"},{"time":906000,"text":"more than 75 percent of the population"},{"time":909000,"text":"of those countries are obese."},{"time":912000,"text":"Look a decade ago, look two decades ago: markedly different."},{"time":916000,"text":"So, our systems today are dramatically different"},{"time":919000,"text":"than our systems a decade or two ago."},{"time":923000,"text":"So the diseases we have today,"},{"time":926000,"text":"which reflect patterns in the system over the last several decades,"},{"time":930000,"text":"are going to change dramatically over the next decade or so"},{"time":934000,"text":"based on things like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937000,"text":"So, this picture, although it is beautiful, is a 40-gigabyte picture"},{"time":947000,"text":"of the whole proteome."},{"time":949000,"text":"So this is a drop of blood that has gone through a superconducting magnet,"},{"time":953000,"text":"and we're able to get resolution"},{"time":955000,"text":"where we can start to see all of the proteins in the body."},{"time":959000,"text":"We can start to see that system."},{"time":961000,"text":"Each of the red dots are where a protein has actually been identified."},{"time":965000,"text":"The power of these magnets, the power of what we can do here,"},{"time":967000,"text":"is that we can see an individual neutron with this technology."},{"time":972000,"text":"So, again, this is stuff we're doing with Danny Hillis"},{"time":975000,"text":"and a group called Applied Proteomics,"},{"time":977000,"text":"where we can start to see individual neutron differences,"},{"time":981000,"text":"and we can start to look at that system like we never have before."},{"time":985000,"text":"So, instead of a reductionist view, we're taking a step back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":989000,"text":"So this is a woman, 46 years old,"},{"time":993000,"text":"who had recurrent lung cancer."},{"time":996000,"text":"It was in her brain, in her lungs, in her liver."},{"time":1000000,"text":"She had gotten Carboplatin Taxol, Carboplatin Taxotere,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"Gemcitabine, Navelbine:"},{"time":1006000,"text":"Every drug we have she had gotten, and that disease continued to grow."},{"time":1011000,"text":"She had three kids under the age of 12,"},{"time":1015000,"text":"and this is her CT scan."},{"time":1017000,"text":"And so what this is, is we're taking a cross-section of her body here,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"and you can see in the middle there is her heart,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"and to the side of her heart on the left there is this large tumor"},{"time":1027000,"text":"that will invade and will kill her, untreated, in a matter of weeks."},{"time":1033000,"text":"She goes on a pill a day that targets a pathway,"},{"time":1038000,"text":"and again, I'm not sure if this pathway was in the system, in the cancer,"},{"time":1042000,"text":"but it targeted a pathway, and a month later, pow, that cancer's gone."},{"time":1048000,"text":"Six months later it's still gone."},{"time":1051000,"text":"That cancer recurred, and she passed away three years later from lung cancer,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"but she got three years from a drug"},{"time":1060000,"text":"whose symptoms predominately were acne."},{"time":1062000,"text":"That's about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1064000,"text":"So, the problem is that the clinical trial was done,"},{"time":1068000,"text":"and we were a part of it,"},{"time":1070000,"text":"and in the fundamental clinical trial --"},{"time":1072000,"text":"the pivotal clinical trial we call the Phase Three,"},{"time":1074000,"text":"we refused to use a placebo."},{"time":1077000,"text":"Would you want your mother, your brother, your sister"},{"time":1079000,"text":"to get a placebo if they had advanced lung cancer and had weeks to live?"},{"time":1083000,"text":"And the answer, obviously, is not."},{"time":1085000,"text":"So, it was done on this group of patients."},{"time":1087000,"text":"Ten percent of people in the trial had this dramatic response that was shown here,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"and the drug went to the FDA,"},{"time":1096000,"text":"and the FDA said, \"Without a placebo,"},{"time":1098000,"text":"how do I know patients actually benefited from the drug?\""},{"time":1103000,"text":"So the morning the FDA was going to meet,"},{"time":1105000,"text":"this was the editorial in the Wall Street Journal."},{"time":1108000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1110000,"text":"And so, what do you know, that drug was approved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1114000,"text":"The amazing thing is another company did the right scientific trial,"},{"time":1118000,"text":"where they gave half placebo and half the drug."},{"time":1121000,"text":"And we learned something important there."},{"time":1123000,"text":"What's interesting is they did it in South America and Canada,"},{"time":1126000,"text":"where it's \"more ethical to give placebos.\""},{"time":1129000,"text":"They had to give it also in the U.S. to get approval,"},{"time":1131000,"text":"so I think there were three U.S. patients"},{"time":1133000,"text":"in upstate New York who were part of the trial."},{"time":1135000,"text":"But they did that, and what they found"},{"time":1137000,"text":"is that 70 percent of the non-responders"},{"time":1140000,"text":"lived much longer and did better than people who got placebo."},{"time":1145000,"text":"So it challenged everything we knew in cancer,"},{"time":1148000,"text":"is that you don't need to get a response."},{"time":1150000,"text":"You don't need to shrink the disease."},{"time":1152000,"text":"If we slow the disease, we may have more of a benefit"},{"time":1156000,"text":"on patient survival, patient outcome, how they feel,"},{"time":1160000,"text":"than if we shrink the disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1162000,"text":"The problem is that, if I'm this doc, and I get your CT scan today"},{"time":1165000,"text":"and you've got a two centimeter mass in your liver,"},{"time":1168000,"text":"and you come back to me in three months and it's three centimeters,"},{"time":1171000,"text":"did that drug help you or not?"},{"time":1173000,"text":"How do I know?"},{"time":1175000,"text":"Would it have been 10 centimeters, or am I giving you a drug"},{"time":1179000,"text":"with no benefit and significant cost?"},{"time":1182000,"text":"So, it's a fundamental problem."},{"time":1184000,"text":"And, again, that's where these new technologies can come in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1189000,"text":"And so, the goal obviously is that you go into your doctor's office --"},{"time":1193000,"text":"well, the ultimate goal is that you prevent disease, right?"},{"time":1196000,"text":"The ultimate goal is that you prevent any of these things from happening."},{"time":1200000,"text":"That is the most effective, cost-effective,"},{"time":1203000,"text":"best way we can do things today."},{"time":1205000,"text":"But if one is unfortunate to get a disease,"},{"time":1208000,"text":"you'll go into your doctor's office, he or she will take a drop of blood,"},{"time":1211000,"text":"and we will start to know how to treat your disease."},{"time":1216000,"text":"The way we've approached it is the field of proteomics,"},{"time":1219000,"text":"again, this looking at the system."},{"time":1221000,"text":"It's taking a big picture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1223000,"text":"The problem with technologies like this is"},{"time":1226000,"text":"that if one looks at proteins in the body,"},{"time":1228000,"text":"there are 11 orders of magnitude difference"},{"time":1231000,"text":"between the high-abundant and the low-abundant proteins."},{"time":1234000,"text":"So, there's no technology in the world that can span 11 orders of magnitude."},{"time":1239000,"text":"And so, a lot of what has been done with people like Danny Hillis and others"},{"time":1244000,"text":"is to try to bring in engineering principles, try to bring the software."},{"time":1248000,"text":"We can start to look at different components along this spectrum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1253000,"text":"And so, earlier was talked about cross-discipline, about collaboration."},{"time":1258000,"text":"And I think one of the exciting things that is starting to happen now"},{"time":1261000,"text":"is that people from those fields are coming in."},{"time":1264000,"text":"Yesterday, the National Cancer Institute announced a new program"},{"time":1267000,"text":"called the Physical Sciences and Oncology,"},{"time":1270000,"text":"where physicists, mathematicians, are brought in to think about cancer,"},{"time":1274000,"text":"people who never approached it before."},{"time":1277000,"text":"Danny and I got 16 million dollars, they announced yesterday,"},{"time":1280000,"text":"to try to attach this problem."},{"time":1282000,"text":"A whole new approach, instead of giving high doses of chemotherapy"},{"time":1286000,"text":"by different mechanisms,"},{"time":1288000,"text":"to try to bring technology to get a picture of what's actually happening in the body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1294000,"text":"So, just for two seconds, how these technologies work --"},{"time":1298000,"text":"because I think it's important to understand it."},{"time":1301000,"text":"What happens is every protein in your body is charged,"},{"time":1304000,"text":"so the proteins are sprayed in, the magnet spins them around,"},{"time":1308000,"text":"and then there's a detector at the end."},{"time":1310000,"text":"When it hit that detector is dependent on the mass and the charge."},{"time":1315000,"text":"And so we can accurately -- if the magnet is big enough,"},{"time":1318000,"text":"and your resolution is high enough --"},{"time":1320000,"text":"you can actually detect all of the proteins in the body"},{"time":1323000,"text":"and start to get an understanding of the individual system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1327000,"text":"And so, as a cancer doctor,"},{"time":1329000,"text":"instead of having paper in my chart, in your chart, and it being this thick,"},{"time":1334000,"text":"this is what data flow is starting to look like in our offices,"},{"time":1338000,"text":"where that drop of blood is creating gigabytes of data."},{"time":1341000,"text":"Electronic data elements are describing every aspect of the disease."},{"time":1345000,"text":"And certainly the goal is we can start to learn from every encounter"},{"time":1349000,"text":"and actually move forward, instead of just having encounter and encounter,"},{"time":1354000,"text":"without fundamental learning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1356000,"text":"So, to conclude, we need to get away from reductionist thinking."},{"time":1362000,"text":"We need to start to think differently and radically."},{"time":1366000,"text":"And so, I implore everyone here: Think differently. Come up with new ideas."},{"time":1370000,"text":"Tell them to me or anyone else in our field,"},{"time":1373000,"text":"because over the last 59 years, nothing has changed."},{"time":1376000,"text":"We need a radically different approach."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1379000,"text":"You know, Andy Grove stepped down as chairman of the board at Intel --"},{"time":1382000,"text":"and Andy was one of my mentors, tough individual."},{"time":1385000,"text":"When Andy stepped down, he said,"},{"time":1387000,"text":"\"No technology will win. Technology itself will win.\""},{"time":1390000,"text":"And I'm a firm believer, in the field of medicine and especially cancer,"},{"time":1394000,"text":"that it's going to be a broad platform of technologies"},{"time":1397000,"text":"that will help us move forward"},{"time":1399000,"text":"and hopefully help patients in the near-term."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1401000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}